8 Naypyidaw]]|Elite time trial}}\n{{MedalBronze|[[2017 Asian Cycling Championships|2017 Manama]]|Elite time trial}}\n{{MedalBronze|[[2017 Asian Cycling Championships|2017 Manama]]|Team time trial}}\n{{MedalBronze|[[2018 Asian Cycling Championships|2018 Naypyidaw]]|Team time trial}}\n{{MedalBronze|[[2019 Asian Road Cycling Championships|2019 Tashkent]]|Elite time trial}}\n| show-medals = no\n}}\n'''Cheung King Lok''' (born 8 February 1991) is a Hong Kong professional [[bicycle racing|racing cyclist]], who currently rides for [[UCI Continental team]] {{ct|HKS}}.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.uci.org/road/teams/TeamDetail/14085/1001263/257|title=HKSI Pro Cycling Team|work=UCI.org|publisher=[[Union Cycliste Internationale]]|accessdate=3 April 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200403223506/https://www.uci.org/road/teams/TeamDetail/14085/1001263/257|archivedate=3 April 2020}}</ref> He rode at the [[2015 UCI Track Cycling World Championships]].<ref name=\"UCI\">{{cite web |url=http://www.uci.ch/mm/Document/News/NewsGeneral/16/85/15/20150212_SQEY_ME_EntryListUCIwebsite_English.PDF |title=Entry List: Men |accessdate=25 February 2015 |work=UCI}}</ref> He competed in the 2010 and 2014 [[Asian Games]] and won several medals.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.incheon2014ag.org/Sports/Biographies/Athletes_Profile/?ParticCode=5117946&lang=en|title=Profile|work=Incheon 2014 official website|accessdate=12 July 2015|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150924045857/http://www.incheon2014ag.org/Sports/Biographies/Athletes_Profile/?ParticCode=5117946&lang=en|archivedate=24 September 2015}}</ref> He joined {{ct|ORS|2016a}} as a neo-pro in mid-2016,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.greenedgecycling.com/team/mens/cheung-king-lok |title=Cheung King Lok|accessdate=25 April 2017}}</ref> remaining with the team until the end of 2017, before returning to [[UCI Continental]] level with {{ct|HKS|2018}}.\n\n==Major results==\n===Road===\n{{Div col}}\n;2009\n: 1st Time trial, Asian Junior Road Championships\n;2010\n: 1st Stage 10 [[Tour de Korea]]\n: 4th Time trial, [[2010 Asian Cycling Championships|Asian Road Championships]]\n;2011\n: 1st [[File:China NC.png|20px]] Time trial, Chinese National Road Championships{{efn|name=China|Cheung King Lok competed for China prior to 2014, so was eligible to race in the 2013 Chinese National Time Trial championships, afterwards, from 2014 to 2016 he represented Hong Kong and as such competed in the Hong Kong National cycling championships, reverting to China in 2017.}}\n: 3rd Road race, Hong Kong National Under-23 Road Championships\n;2012\n: 1st [[File:Jersey white.svg|20px]] Young rider classification [[Tour de Kumano]]\n: 2nd Time trial, Chinese National Road Championships{{efn|name=China}}\n: 4th Overall [[Tour of Taihu Lake]]\n: 10th Overall [[Tour of Hainan]]\n::1st Stage 6\n;2013\n: 1st [[File:China NC.png|20px]] Time trial, Chinese National Road Championships{{efn|name=China}}\n: Hong Kong National Road Championships\n::2nd Time trial\n::3rd Road race\n: 2nd Overall [[Tour de Korea]]\n::1st [[File:Jersey white.svg|20px]] Young rider classification\n: [[2013 Asian Cycling Championships|Asian Under-23 Road Championships]]\n::4th Road race\n::6th Time trial\n: 7th Overall [[Tour of Thailand]]\n: 8th Overall [[Tour of China]] I\n;2014\n: Hong Kong National Road Championships\n::1st [[File:Hong Kong NC.png|20px]] Road race\n::1st [[File:Hong Kong NC.png|20px]] Time trial\n: 2nd Overall [[Tour of Thailand]]\n: 6th Time trial, [[2014 Asian Cycling Championships|Asian Road Championships]]\n: 9th Overall [[Tour de Korea]]\n;2015\n: 1st [[File:Hong Kong NC.png|20px]] Time trial, Hong Kong National Road Championships\n: 3rd Overall [[Tour of Thailand]]\n: 3rd Overall [[Jelajah Malaysia]]\n: 7th Overall [[Tour de Ijen]]\n::1st Stage 1\n: 10th Overall [[Tour of Fuzhou]]\n;2016\n: [[2016 Asian Cycling Championships|Asian Road Championships]]\n::1st Time trial\n::1st Road race\n: Hong Kong National R